African Capital to Own 60 Percent of Union Bank, Nation Says

-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 
2011-09-12T08:24:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-12/african-capital-to-own-60-percent-of-union-bank-nation-says.html
African Capital Alliance
Consortium, the main shareholder in  Union Bank Nigeria Plc (UBN) , will
own 60 percent of the lender at the end of its recapitalization,
The Nation  reported , citing the deputy manager in charge of
treasury, Abayomi Oluyomi.  Shareholders of the lender bailed out by the central bank
in 2009 will get 21 percent while the state-owned Asset
Management Corp. of  Nigeria  will hold 19 percent equity, the
Lagos-based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
 ebalagbogbo@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 